text=:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild%0a:Essential: {Category.LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild$:essential}%0a:Title: Accent Discrimination in Education%0a:Author: Simon_Y%0a:Section: A%0a:Completed: 24.04.2021 - 23:07%0a:Status: complete%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a----%0a%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%0a[[#history]]%0a#foxbegin 210504-191224-216660#%0a* [-04.05.2021 - 12:12-] || TA_audrey marked as complete%0a#foxend 210504-191224-216660#%0a[[#historyend]]%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Comments for student'''%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a%0a[[#commentsend]]%0a%0a----%0a----%0a!!%0a%0aSummary: \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aSome of my thoughts on accent discrimination%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aLink to article:%0ahttps://www.theguardian.com/education/2020/oct/24/uk-top-universities-urged-act-classism-accent-prejudice%0a%0aIn this article, the Guardian investigation has found evidence of discriminatory acts against students with regional accents in some Russel group universities -- UK's counterpart to the Ivy League. Reports and interviews suggest that there is a "toxic" attitude towards students with a regional dialect/pronunciation, such as a northern England accent. The article also points out that this is not only discrimination against accents but also an instance of classism, where students are targets by their socio-economical background.%0a%0aWhile it is sad to believe that communities in Higher Education suffer from issues like this, it certainly exists. When I was in middle school, I participated in an exchange program to a well-reputed grammar school in the UK (a Grammar school in the UK is somewhat equivalent to a private school). Back then, I and some of my friends spoke English with a noticeable accent. By the end of the program, my classmates in the program who spoke with less accent blended into the host school's community much better. Some I have reasons to believe that discrimination does exist in prestigious institutions.%0a%0aAs a second language speaker of English, while I strive to speak the best Standard American English as I could, it is in all of our best interest to combat accent discrimination. After all, the linguistic background is part of your identity.%0a%0a%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a(:GradedBy: TA_audrey:)
