diff:1619330859:1619330859:=1,54d0%0a%3c :Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild%0a%3c :Essential: {Category.LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild$:essential}%0a%3c :Title: Accent Discrimination in Education%0a%3c :Author: Simon_Y%0a%3c :Section: A%0a%3c :Completed: 24.04.2021 - 23:07%0a%3c :Status: ungraded%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %25blue%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#history]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#historyend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c %25blue%25 '''Comments for student'''%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#comments]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#commentsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c !!%0a%3c %0a%3c Summary: \\%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summary]]%0a%3c %0a%3c Some of my thoughts on accent discrimination%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#summaryends]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c Link to article:%0a%3c https://www.theguardian.com/education/2020/oct/24/uk-top-universities-urged-act-classism-accent-prejudice%0a%3c %0a%3c In this article, the Guardian investigation has found evidence of discriminatory acts against students with regional accents in some Russel group universities -- UK's counterpart to the Ivy League. Reports and interviews suggest that there is a "toxic" attitude towards students with a regional dialect/pronunciation, such as a northern England accent. The article also points out that this is not only discrimination against accents but also an instance of classism, where students are targets by their socio-economical background.%0a%3c %0a%3c While it is sad to believe that communities in Higher Education suffer from issues like this, it certainly exists. When I was in middle school, I participated in an exchange program to a well-reputed grammar school in the UK (a Grammar school in the UK is somewhat equivalent to a private school). Back then, I and some of my friends spoke English with a noticeable accent. By the end of the program, my classmates in the program who spoke with less accent blended into the host school's community much better. Some I have reasons to believe that discrimination does exist in prestigious institutions.%0a%3c %0a%3c As a second language speaker of English, while I strive to speak the best Standard American English as I could, it is in all of our best interest to combat accent discrimination. After all, the linguistic background is part of your identity.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
